<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>in glory • in one’s glory</xh5><p> <i>in glory</i>—(of saints, etc.) in heavenly bliss and splendor: The crown is placed on the head of the maternal Virgin <u>in glory</u>. <i>in one’s glory—</i>in one’s highest state of prosperity or enjoyment: I was <u>in my glory</u> when they gave me a standing ovation.</p> </entry>
